companies.name: gojek
companies.description: PT Aplikasi Karya Anak Bangsa, doing business as Gojek (stylized in lower case as gojek), is Southeast Asia's leading on-demand multi-service platform and digital payment technology group.

companies.name: tokopedia
companies.description: Tokopedia is an Indonesian technology company[3], sometimes referred to as a unicorn. It was founded in 2009 by William Tanuwijaya and his best friend, Leontinus Alpha Edison. As of November 2018, the company is valued at about $7 billion.

companies.name: bukalapak
companies.description: Bukalapak is one of the largest e-commerce companies based in Indonesia valued at over US$1 billion.[3][4][5] Founded by Achmad Zaky, Nugroho Herucahyono and Fajrin Rasyid in 2010, Bukalapak initially started as an online marketplace to enable small medium enterprise go online

companies.name: traveloka
companies.description: Traveloka (est. in 2012) is an Indonesian unicorn company that provides airline ticketing and hotel booking services online expanding rapidly into South East Asia[2] and Australia[3]. It recently expanded to provide lifestyle products and services, such as attraction tickets, activities, car rental, and restaurant vouchers.
